    <li>Investment-grade quality</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Food Pairing Guide</h2>

  <h3>Perfect Matches</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Grilled salmon and herb-crusted chicken</li>
    <li>Mushroom risotto and roasted vegetables</li>
    <li>Soft cheeses like Brie and Camembert</li>
    <li>Charcuterie and Mediterranean dishes</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Avoid Pairing With</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Very spicy foods that overpower the wine</li>
    <li>Heavy cream sauces that mask the fruit</li>
    <li>Strong blue cheeses that compete</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Storage & Serving</h2>

  <p>**Storage Temperature**: 55-60°F in wine refrigerator</p>

  <p>**Serving Temperature**: 60-65°F (slightly chilled)</p>

  <p>**Decanting**: Not necessary but can enhance aromatics</p>

  <p>**Glassware**: Burgundy-style glasses with wide bowl</p>

  <h2>Investment Potential</h2>

  <p>Chardonnay from top producers can age 10-15 years and appreciate in value. Look for limited releases and vineyard-designate wines.</p>

